Course will give basic knowledge about information systems, concepts related to information systems, will introduce general operational logic of information systems, how systems affect the organization and the system development life cycle. Also, students will learn state information system information architecture, why it is important and what are the possibilities.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the role of information systems in a modern organization. The course will introduce the types, development, and management of information systems and will give overview of the state information system information architecture.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: - knows and is able to use basic concepts related to information systems and databases and knows how they relate (also open data, big data); - knows about information systems role in modern organization; - is able to name basic problems related to information systems privacy issuses and ethics; - knows about information system types which help to support organizations main processes and knows their general operational logic; - knows about information system types which help to support organizations support processes and knows their general operational logic; - knows what is organizations IT infrastructure, knows how to describe its functioning and management; - knows about information systems development process, how it affects the organization, and what to consider while implementing information systems; - knows what is state information system information architecture and why it is important;
